      • setTableNamePattern

        public void setTableNamePattern(java.lang.String tableNamePattern)
        Sets the table name pattern, using the JDBC syntax for wildcards (_ and *). The table name pattern is case-sensitive, and matches just the table name - not the fully qualified table name. The table name pattern restricts the tables retrieved at an early stage in the retrieval process, so it must be used only when performance needs to be tuned. A null value indicates do not take table pattern into account.
        Parameters:
        tableNamePattern - Table name pattern, null is allowed

      • setTableTypes

        public void setTableTypes(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> tableTypes)
        Sets table types requested for output from a collection of table types. For example: TABLE,VIEW,SYSTEM_TABLE,GLOBAL TEMPORARY,ALIAS,SYNONYM
        Parameters:
        tableTypes - Collection of table types. Can be null if all supported table types are requested.
